  "prompt": "Where can I find a power outlet for my laptop at Melbourne Airport?",
  "response": "At Melbourne Airport, you can find power outlets for your laptop in various locations throughout the terminals. Here are some common places to check:\n\n1. **Airline Lounges**: Most airline lounges have power outlets available for guests. If you are a member of a lounge, this can be a convenient option.\n\n2. **Seating Areas**: Many seating areas, especially near gates and in the terminal hallways, are equipped with power outlets.\n\n3. **Charging Stations**: Look for dedicated charging stations which are often located in communal seating areas or near departure gates.\n\n4. **Cafes and Restaurants**: Some cafes and restaurants may have outlets near tables, allowing you to charge your device while you enjoy a meal or a drink.\n\n5. **Business Facilities**: If you're traveling for work, check if there are business centers in the airport that may have workstations with power outlets.\n\nMake sure to keep an eye out for signs that indicate the availability of power outlets. If you're unsure, airport staff can also assist you in finding an outlet.",
